            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Thrombocythemia with distal limb defects is a rare genetic syndrome with limb reduction defects characterized by thrombocytosis unilateral transverse limb defects (ranging from absence of phalanges to absence of hand or forearm) and splenomegaly."
